> FNMR(σ) = |{Is ∈ 𝒮_low-quality | Q(Is) ≥ σ}| / |{Is | Q(Is) ≥ σ}|

This means FNMR measures the rate at which low-quality samples (from 𝒮_low-quality) are incorrectly accepted by the model Q when the quality threshold σ is applied. In other words, it quantifies false acceptances of low-quality scans.

